<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 8684/3.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Swedish
                                        Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-12"><hi rend="italic">October 12,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 36.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the department’s note of
                                the 4th instant in regard to the proposed increase of taxes in Cairo
                                with a view to the construction of a sewer system, I have the honor
                                to say that the agent of the United States at Cairo having reported
                                that American interests will be slightly, if at all, affected by the
                                proposed increase of the tax on rental valuation of realty, he has
                                been instructed that he may assent thereto, if the assent of the
                                United States be necessary to insure unanimity.</p>
                            <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A.
                                Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>